Ashley Tillman (she/her) is a dance movement artist living and operating in Brooklyn, NY. In 2019, she graduated from the University of the Arts with a BFA in Dance under the direction of Donna Faye Burchfield and a minor in Business. Her studies granted her the opportunity to work with artists such as Doug Varone, Beth Gill, Netta Yerushalmy, Bobbi Jene Smith, among others. Ashley’s work explores excavating bodily layers of information through spectrums of intimacy & the radical, somatic entry, and improvisational dreaming. Upon graduating, her interests have lead her to delve into arts administration, Pilates education, and a personal ceramics practice.
